      "repair_reason": "Human handling is needed because contributor live proof and maintainer approval for ACP attachment policy are merge blockers before mechanical cleanup is safe.; Needs attention: Needs attention because the diff rewrites shrinkwrap provenance and expands inline attachment forwarding into ACP runtimes.; Review finding: [P1] Send ACP images in the gateway RPC shape — src/agents/acp-spawn.ts:1466-1468 - [P1] Remove the... (sha=8dd0e007cda8bd09b8d3f5b50a082133ca18966b)",
      "review_summary": "The PR enables image attachments for `sessions_spawn(runtime=\"acp\")`, forwards them toward ACP run turns, updates agent tests/docs/changelog, and refreshes many root/plugin npm shrinkwrap files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: current main rejects `sessions_spawn(runtime=\"acp\")` attachments before dispatch. I did not establish a live ACP/Codex image run in this read-only review.",
