      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix #78919: [Bug] ACP sessions_spawn doesn't route images to Codex's native vision like acpx codex exec does",
        "body": "## Summary\nFixes #78919\n\n### Issue\n[[Bug] ACP sessions_spawn doesn't route images to Codex's native vision like acpx codex exec does](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/78919)\n\n### Changes\n- fix(agents): route image attachments through sessions_spawn ACP path to Codex native vision\n\n### Changed Files\n```\nCHANGELOG.md                                 |  1 +\n src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts                 | 72 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n src/agents/acp-spawn.ts                      | 24 ++++++++++\n src/agents/agent-command.ts                  |  3 ++\n src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts | 25 +++++++---\n src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.ts      |  9 +---\n 6 files changed, 119 insertions(+), 15 deletions(-)\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed**: When calling `sessions_spawn(runtime=acp)` with image attachments, the tool rejected them with \"attachments are currently unsupported for runtime=acp\". Meanwhile, `acpx codex exec` correctly forwarded images to Codex native vision. The images were silently dropped instead of being routed through the ACP gateway agent call.\n\n**Real environment tested**: OpenClaw dev checkout on Linux (CentOS 8), Node 22, with `pnpm tsc` type checking and unit tests via `pnpm test`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch**:\n```bash\ncd /media/vdc/code/ai/openclaw-78919\npnpm install\nnpx tsc --noEmit\npnpm test src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts\npnpm test src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\nTerminal output from tsc and test runs confirms the fix compiles and tests pass:\n```\n$ npx tsc --noEmit\n(no errors)\n\n$ pnpm test src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts\n ✓ acp-spawn > toRpcAttachments > converts utf8 attachment to base64\n ✓ acp-spawn > toRpcAttachments > preserves base64 attachment\n ✓ acp-spawn > toRpcAttachments > forwards mimeType when present\n\n$ pnpm test src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts\n ✓ sessions_spawn tool > ACP runtime > forwards attachments to spawnAcpDirect instead of rejecting\n```\nThe code change removes the early-return error block that rejected attachments for `runtime=acp`, and instead forwards them through `spawnAcpDirect` → `acpManager.runTurn` via the new `toRpcAttachments` helper that encodes images to base64 for the RPC call.\n\n**Observed result after fix**: `sessions_spawn(runtime=acp)` no longer rejects image attachments. Images are forwarded through the ACP path via `toRpcAttachments` and `acpManager.runTurn`, matching the working `acpx codex exec` image routing path. TypeScript compilation and all related unit tests pass cleanly.\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end live gateway test with actual Codex vision model (tested via unit test coverage only).",
